## Annotation Format

Every reversed `.c` file starts with a **stable identity header** — only the
information that is intrinsic to the function and never changes:

```c
// FUNCTION: {target_name} 0x<virtual_address>
// SYMBOL: _function_name                 ← optional, derived from C definition

void __cdecl function_name(void)
{{
    // stub
}}
```

Volatile metadata (status, size, compiler flags, notes, blockers) is stored
**outside** the `.c` file in a per-directory `rebrew-functions.toml` sidecar file:

```toml
[0x10001234]
status = "STUB"
size   = 42
cflags = "/O2 /Gd"
blocker = "register allocation"
note   = "inline asm detected"
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never manually edit `rebrew-functions.toml`.** It is managed exclusively by Rebrew
> CLI tools (`rebrew promote`, `rebrew test`, `rebrew match`, etc.).  Manual
> edits will be lost or corrupt the file and break tool workflows.

**STATUS values**: `EXACT` (byte-perfect) > `RELOC` (match after masking
relocations) > `MATCHING` (close) > `STUB` (incomplete)

`CFLAGS` is optional — falls back to the target default from `rebrew-project.toml`.

